<Link id="l00154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="154"><Highlight kind="comment">/// have one or more associated dbg&#95;value entries. This information is kept in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="155"><Highlight kind="comment">/// DbgValMap.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="157"><Highlight kind="comment">/// which busts the normal mechanism.  There is good reason for handling all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158"><Highlight kind="comment">/// parameters separately:  they may not have code generated for them, they</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159"><Highlight kind="comment">/// should always go at the beginning of the function regardless of other code</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><Highlight kind="comment">/// motion, and debug info for them is potentially useful even if the parameter</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is unused.  Right now only byval parameters are handled separately.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2049"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Return the number of times the sign bit of the register is replicated into</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2050"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the other bits. We know that at least 1 bit is always equal to the sign</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2051"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// bit (itself), but other cases can give us information. For example,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2052"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// immediately after an &quot;SRA X, 2&quot;, we know that the top 3 bits are all equal</Highlight></CodeLine>
